class {
    the class contains the properties and methods of the object
    it is a blueprint of the object
    it is a template for creating objects
    it is a useful design pattern for code reuse and organization
    it can be applied to many elements in the html document
}
id{
    the id is a unique identifier for an element in the html document
    it is used to target specific elements with css and javascript
    it should be unique within the document, meaning that no two elements should have the same id
}
link icon{
    the link icon is used to specify the icon for a webpage
    it is typically displayed in the browser tab or bookmark list
    it can be specified using the <link> element in the head of the html document
    it can be in various formats such as .ico, .png, .svg, etc.
}
svg{
    svg stands for Scalable Vector Graphics
    it is a vector image format that can be scaled to any size without losing quality
    it is commonly used for icons, logos, and illustrations on the web
    it can be created and edited using various software such as Adobe Illustrator, Inkscape, etc.
    it can be embedded directly in the html document using the <svg> element or linked as an external file
    it can be styled and animated using css and javascript
}
p{
    the <p> element is used to define a paragraph in the html document
    it is a block-level element that creates a new line before and after it
    it can contain text, images, and other inline elements
    it can be styled using css to change its appearance, such as font size, color, background, etc.
    it is a default state is diplayed as a block element, meaning it takes up the full width of its container and starts on a new line
}
a{
    the <a> element is used to create a hyperlink in the html document
    it can link to another webpage, a specific section of the same page, an email address, or a file
    it is typically displayed as underlined text, but can be styled using css to change its appearance
    it can have various attributes such as href (the destination of the link), target (where to open the link), title (additional information about the link), etc.
    it is a default state is displayed as an inline element, meaning it does not start on a new line and only takes up as much width as necessaryase
}
